The Senate, on Tuesday, adjourned its post-Easter holiday resumption to Wednesday, April 27, in honour of Hon. Ekpenyong Nse Bassey who died on Sunday in Uyo, at 4 pm. Until his death, the late Bassey was a member representing Oron Federal Constituency of Akwa Ibom State in the House of Representatives. Tuesday sitting was presided over by the Deputy President of the Senate, Ovie Omo-Agege (Delta Central). The motion for adjournment was moved by the Deputy Leader, Ajayi Boroffice, and seconded by the Minority Whip, Senator Philip Aduda. The Senate, moments before adjourning till Wednesday, held a minute silence to mourn the demise of the lawmaker.